					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>The king's name and the date are lost, the inscription being badly damaged. This seems to register a gift of 7(1/2) <hi rend="italic">mā</hi> of land after reclamation and 15 <hi rend="italic">kāśu</hi> (probably towards the land tax) from Kūḍalūruḍaiyāṉ Sōman••••••••• vana-Nāḍāḻvāṉ who is called the “Daṇḍanāyaka of the Paḷḷichchivigaiyār of the Perundaram,” for the purpose of burning a perpetual lamp in the temple.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
